[[File:Pula Lighting Giants.jpg|thumb|Skiras light design on cranes in Pula harbour]]'''Dean Skira''' (born 20 October 1962) is a [[Croatia]]n lighting designer.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jim Powell |url=https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/gallery/2013/apr/13/observer-20-photographs-of-week |title=The Observer's 20 photographs of the week &#124; From the Observer |publisher=theguardian.com |date= |accessdate=2018-09-06}}</ref> Skira founded his own lighting design practice in 1990 in [[New York City]], USA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.new4amagazine.com/2012/02/sustainable-talk-with-lighting-designer.html |title=4aMagazine: A sustainable talk with the lighting designer Dean Skira |publisher=New4amagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2018-09-06}}</ref> He lives and works in [[Pula, Croatia]].
In 1986 Skira studied lighting and interior design at the [[Fashion Institute of Technology]] in [[New York City]]. Since 1995 he and his team of designers and engineers have based their work in Croatia.
Skira is a member of IALD International Association of Lighting Designers, IES The Illuminating Engineering Society of North America, New York section. He is also affiliated with the Croatian Designers Society and Croatian Lighting Association.
One of Skira's best known projects is the "Lighting Giants", in Pula, Croatia, which changed the shipping cranes at the Uljanik Shipyard into a moving lighted art installation.<ref>[http://news.artnet.com/art-world/shipyard-cranes-come-alive-in-mesmerizing-croatian-light-projection-32178 "Shipyard Cranes Come Alive in Mesmerizing Croatian Light Projection"]. ''ArtNetNews''.</ref>
== Notable projects == * Eurasia Underwater Tunnel, Istanbul, Turkey (2016) * TSUM, Kyiv, Ukraine (2017) * Roundabout Pula, Croatia (2017) * Hendrix Bridge, Zagreb, Croatia (2017) * Twisted, installation (2016) * Eggotrick, installation (2018) * Cikat Bay Resort, Losinj, Croatia (2015) * Postojna Cave, Postojna, Slovenia (2013) * Biennale Arte, Italian, pavilion, Venice (2013) * Hooked up installation, Milano (2013) * Parco della Luna, Recanati, Italy (2012) * Design hotel Lone landscape, Rovinj, Croatia (2011) * Policlinic Novamed, Zagreb, Croatia (2010) * Park Eden landscape, Rovinj, Croatia * Novamed polyclinic, Zagreb, Croatia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enlightermagazine.com/projects/novamed-polyclinic-skira-lighting |title=Novamed Polyclinic by Skira lighting design |publisher=Enlighter Magazine |date= |accessdate=2018-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bdonline.co.uk/cpd-6-2014-sustainable-lighting/5066837.article |title=CPD 6 2014: Sustainable lighting &#124; Features &#124; Building Design |publisher=Bdonline.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2018-09-06}}</ref> * Rident polyclinic, Poreč, Croatia * Novi Spa & Resort, Novi Vinodolski, Croatia<ref>[http://content.yudu.com/Library/A1z3bt/MondoArcOctNov2012Is/resources/36.htm "Snapshot"] Mondo*Arc, Oct/Nov2012 Issue 69</ref> * Hotel Argentina, Dubrovnik, Croatia * Arena(lighting control system), Zagreb, Croatia * Four Seasons Hotel, Baku, Azerbaijan * Hotel Kempinski, Savudrija, Croatia (2009) * Spa&Hotel Novi Resort, Novi Vinodolski, Croatia (2008) * Memorial Centre Dražen Petrović, Zagreb, Croatia (2006) * Town of Buzet, Croatia (2001) * Cranes Pula, Croatia (2014) <ref>Hawkins, Si. [http://www.letsgo-mag.com/story/lighting-the-way/1455/1/ "Lighting the Way"]. ''Let's Go with Rynair''.</ref><ref>[http://www.dezeen.com/2014/05/31/croatian-designer-creates-giant-light-show-by-illuminating-shipyard-cranes/ "Croatian designer creates giant light show by illuminating shipyard cranes]. ''De Zeen''.</ref>
== Awards and recognitions == * IES Award, New York, Eurasia tunnel Award of Merit (2017) * Darc Award, London, Twisted Winner (2017) * Blueprint Award, London, Trick (2015) * "Delta of Gold" Prize at the 2014 Festival of Art and Design.<ref>[http://www.icandela.com/en/notices/2014/07/prizes_delta_2014_the_luminaria_trick_of_the_designer_dean_skira_for_iguzzini_wins_the_delta_of_g_1805.php ""Prizes Delta 2014: the light Trick, of the designer Dean Skira for iGuzzini, wins the Delta of Gold"]. ''ICANDELA''.</ref> * Codega Prize for best LED installation<ref>[http://www.mondoarc.com/news/2133381/designer_dean_skira_wins_inaugural_codega_prize.html "Designer Dean Skira wins inaugural Codega Prize"]. ''MondoArc'', 25 October 2013</ref> * Illumni Infinity award (2013) * iF product design award (2013) * 29th IALD Special citation Award (2012)<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.lighting.co.uk/news/broken-light-wins-iald-radiance-award/8630230.article |title=Broken Light wins IALD Radiance Award {{!}} News {{!}} Lighting |access-date=2014-03-04 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140204064823/http://www.lighting.co.uk/news/broken-light-wins-iald-radiance-award/8630230.article |archive-date= 2014-02-04 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://lighting.com/29th-iald-awards/ |title=29th IALD Awards: Daglicht & Vorm Win Radiance |publisher=lighting.com |date= |accessdate= 2018-09-06}}</ref> * LDA Winner External Luminaire (2012) * The ARC Show Innovation Award (2012) * IESNA Award of Merit (2009) * International prize Dedalo Minosse for Commissioning a Building (2007-2008) * [[Lutron]] most Unusual Installation in Europe (2006) * IESNA Award of Merit (2002)
