[[File:MinnesotaGovMansion.JPG|thumb|right|The Minnesota Governor's Mansion typically also is the residence of the First Spouse]] The spouse of the [[Governor of Minnesota]] is given an honorary position, styled as First Lady or First Gentleman of the State of [[Minnesota]]. To date there have been no female governors of the State of Minnesota, and all First Spouses have been First Ladies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Governors of Minnesota: First Ladies|url=http://www.mnhs.org/people/governors/first_ladies.htm|work=[[Minnesota Historical Society]]|accessdate=23 March 2018}}</ref>
There is no current First Lady, as the Governor, [[Mark Dayton]], is unmarried.
