'''Tang Kesan''' ({{zh|s=唐柯三|t=唐柯三|p=Táng Kēsān}}) was a [[Hui people|Chinese Muslim]]. In [[Xikang]] province during the [[Sino-Tibetan War]] Tang Kesan represented the [[Kuomintang]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?ei=hBshTPqEIsGqlAf_9rDHBA&ct=result&id=0bsKAAAAYAAJ&dq=ma+bufang+liu+wenhui&q=ma+bufang|title=The biographies of the Dalai Lamas|author1=Hanzhang Ya |author2=Ya Hanzhang |year=1991|publisher=Foreign Languages Press|location=|pages=352, 355|isbn=0-8351-2266-2|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

== Career ==
Tang was a Muslim from [[Shandong]] province, and he promoted Muslim education. He worked with Muslim General [[Bai Chongxi]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MJzB6wrz6Q4C&dq=tang+kesan&q=tang+kesan#v=snippet&q=tang%20kesan%20shandong%20chaired%20education&f=false|title=Intellectuals in the modern Islamic world: transmission, transformation, communication|author1=Stéphane A. Dudoignon |author2=Hisao Komatsu |author3=Yasushi Kosugi |year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|location=|page=246|isbn=978-0-415-36835-3|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MJzB6wrz6Q4C&dq=tang+kesan&q=tang+kesan#v=snippet&q=tang%20kesan%20shandong%20activist%20muslim%20education&f=false|title=Intellectuals in the modern Islamic world: transmission, transformation, communication|author1=Stéphane A. Dudoignon |author2=Hisao Komatsu |author3=Yasushi Kosugi |year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|location=|page=365|isbn=978-0-415-36835-3|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> Tang directed the Muslim Chengda School, and was friends with Muslim General [[Ma Fuxiang]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MJzB6wrz6Q4C&pg=PA250&dq=tang+kesan&hl=en&ei=kH2uTMSpNYL48AbChoi-BA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAg#v=snippet&q=tang%20kesan%20chengda%20case&f=false|title=Intellectuals in the modern Islamic world: transmission, transformation, communication|author1=Stéphane A. Dudoignon |author2=Hisao Komatsu |author3=Yasushi Kosugi |year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|location=|page=250|isbn=978-0-415-36835-3|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

Tang negotiated a ceasefire with the Tibetans in 1932.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ak3SQTVS7acC&pg=PA150&dq=tang+kesan&hl=en&ei=VH2uTNivA8P48AbSs8DqBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDgQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=tang%20kesan&f=false|title=The historical status of China's Tibet|author=Jiawei Wang, Nimajianzan|year=1997|publisher=五洲传播出版社|location=|page=150|isbn=7-80113-304-8|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ojhuAAAAMAAJ&q=tang+kesan&dq=tang+kesan&hl=en&ei=hH2uTN-cFoO88gbz3OzcBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CCkQ6AEwATge|title=Le 9e Panchen Lama (1883-1937): enjeu des relations sino-tibétaines|author1=Fabienne Jagou |author2=École française d'Extrême-Orient |year=2004|publisher=École française d'Extrême-Orient|location=|page=233|isbn=2-85539-632-8|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8sL_qNEH1PIC&pg=PA169&dq=tang+kesan&hl=en&ei=Z32uTOf0BIL-8Aaw1Im8BA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CDsQ6AEwBTgK#v=onepage&q=tang%20kesan&f=false|title=中国西藏的历史地位德|year=|publisher=五洲传播出版社|location=|page=169|isbn=7-5085-0257-4|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

[[Ma Fuxiang]], as head of the [[Mongolian and Tibetan Affairs Commission]], sent a telegraph to Tang Kesan ordering him to breach the agreement with Tibet, because he was concerned that political rivals in Nanjing were using the incident.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?ei=MiGVTK5Pw9-WB4D6yKoK&ct=result&id=YD0sAQAAIAAJ&dq=ma+fuxiang+defence&q=Ma+Fuxiang|title=The Journal of the Oriental Society of Australia, Volumes 31-34|author=Oriental Society of Australia|year=2000|publisher=Oriental Society of Australia|location=|page=34|isbn=|pages=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

The President of the education organization Chinese Islamic National Salvation Federation was General [[Bai Chongxi]] (Pai Chung-hsi) and the vice president was Tang Kesan (Tang Ko-san).<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?ei=DeWXU6K7LcKpyASGzIH4Cg&id=1FE8AQAAIAAJ&dq=To+advance+culture+and+education+among+Chinese+Moslem+students%2C+the+Federation+has+obtained+from+the+Ministry+of+Education+substantial&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=federation "The China Monthly, Volumes 3-4" 1941], p. 13.</ref>

